The paper deals with optimization problems in metric spaces, which are typically studied in computer science under the category of "data structures and algorithms" (cs.DS). The problem of metrical service systems is also related to game theory (cs.GT), as it involves competitive analysis of algorithms. The paper also discusses randomized algorithms and approximation algorithms, which are topics studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves analysis of the complexity of algorithms, which is a topic studied in information theory (cs.IT).
